   <head>To a Friend Whose Work Has Come to Nothing</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="???">
     <l n="1" met="-+-+-+">Now all the truth is out,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+--+-+">Be secret and take defeat</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+-+-+">From any brazen throat,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+-+-+">For how can you compete,</l>
     <l n="5" met="--+-+-+">Being honour bred, with one</l>
     <l n="6" met="+--+-+|-+-+-+">Who, were it proved he lies,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+-+--+">Were neither shamed in his own</l>
     <l n="8" met="+--+-+">Nor in his neighbours' eyes?</l>
     <l n="9" met="+--+-+">Bred to a harder thing</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+-+-+">Than Triumph, turn away</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+-+-+">And like a laughing string</l>
     <l n="12" met="--++-+|-+++-+">Whereon mad fingers play</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+-+-+">Amid a place of stone,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+-+-+">Be secret and exult,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+-+++">Because of all things known</l>
     <l n="16" met="+-++-+|+--+-+">That is most difficult.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
